{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Diverting Vortex","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements</strong> Your most recent action was to cast a non-</p>\n<p>cantrip spell.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You transfer vestiges of magical energy to the air around you, creating a vortex that deflects ranged attacks. Until the start of your next turn, you gain a +1 status bonus to AC against ranged weapon attacks and physical ranged unarmed attacks.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Advanced Player's Guide, Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"domain":"ac","key":"RollOption","label":"Use Diverting Vortex","option":"diverting-vortex","toggleable":true},{"key":"FlatModifier","predicate":["ranged","mundane"],"selector":"ac","type":"status","value":1}],"slug":"diverting-vortex","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.PqZZSo06BH5N7x7C"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390119843,"modifiedTime":1666391305248,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"AJJodwRQI7fONLxx","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Widen Spell","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You manipulate the energy of your spell, causing it to spread out and affect a wider area. If the next action you use is to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} that has an area of a burst, cone, or line and does not have a duration, increase the area of that spell. Add 5 feet to the radius of a burst that normally has a radius of at least 10 feet (a burst with a smaller radius is not affected). Add 5 feet to the length of a cone or line that is normally 15 feet long or smaller, and add 10 feet to the length of a larger cone or line</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Core Rulebook, Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["manipulate","metamagic","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"widen-spell","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.FoWO4RnHRwfEIC7Q"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666388688262,"modifiedTime":1666391305247,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"BQmA4YaF1jpxIJYn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Blade of Destruction","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>Your last action was @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-actions.W2XgBLycybWegHqQ]{Divine Force} and your Strike hit</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can channel your deity&rsquo;s wrath through your weapons or fists. Select the weapon you used for your Strike or your handwrap of mighty blows if it was an unarmed attack. It deals an extra 1d6 points of damage to any creature that shares a trait with the target. This benefit lasts until combat is over or until you use this ability again.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":4},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Destruction inquisition"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ra1Wgi4gU0WH6ksL"}},"_id":"C3Iqs6ulvBFn5F3M"}
{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Eschew Materials","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can use clever workarounds to replicate the arcane essence of certain materials. When Casting a Spell that requires material components, you can provide these material components without a spell component pouch by drawing intricate replacement sigils in the air. Unlike when providing somatic components, you still must have a hand completely free. This doesn't remove the need for any materials listed in the spell's cost entry.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Core Rulebook, Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"eschew-materials","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.AD2eQu6SjLhUGD6Z"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666388615300,"modifiedTime":1666391305246,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"CZpgOY651uLXOVF7","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Tradition Tinker","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>When you prepare your spells, you can prepare a single spell as a tradition that it is not normally part of. For example, you could prepare @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.gKKqvLohtrSJj3BM]{Magic Missile} as a divine spell for your daily preparation.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":16},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666391006473,"modifiedTime":1666391305250,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"DzLQywUMzMYuAMHr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Divine Fetters","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You strive to find the perfect prison sentence, sometimes, its life. Once per day, you can cast @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.znv4ECL7ZtuiagtA]{Flesh to Stone} as an innate divine spell of 5th level. This innate spell automatically heightens to match the highest level spell slot you are capable of casting.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":10},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Imprisonment Inquisition"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Tg0IKeTRQl3DUFYX"}},"_id":"E6zirW55Is7LC3dd"}
{"name":"Divine Sight","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>With the power of your deity, nothing is truly hidden from your sight. Once per day, you can cast @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.uqlxMQQeSGWEVjki]{True Seeing} as an innate divine spell of 5th level. This innate spell automatically heightens to match the highest level spell slot you are capable of casting.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":10},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Truth Inquisition"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.IjY0TZtcdKXk9UPa"}},"_id":"E9dbLyw8pHD9YK8Z"}
{"name":"Religious Convert","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>When you attempt to Make a @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.DCb62iCBrJXy0Ik6]{Request} of someone involving the edicts of your deity, you use your Religion skill instead of Diplomacy if the bonus is higher. You may also use your proficiency in Religion in place of Diplomacy to meet the prerequisites of skill feats.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OUI52tnD5rPSpooZ"}},"_id":"EWLWLjpOYb4SQQ2h"}
{"_id":"GPjM1sgp57mdKqsi","name":"Magic Sense","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.AXy4A7zTYk1JAiOV"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have a literal sixth sense for ambient magic in your vicinity.</p>\n<p>You can sense the presence of magic auras as though you were always using a 1st-level <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.gpzpAAAJ1Lza2JVl]{Detect Magic}</em> spell. This detects magic in your field of vision only.</p>\n<p>When you @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.BlAOM2X92SI6HMtJ]{Seek}, you gain the benefits of a 3rd-level <em>detect magic</em> spell on things you see (in addition to the normal benefits of Seeking). You can turn this sense off and on with a free action at the start or the end of your turn.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Advanced Player's Guide, Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["detection","divination","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"magic-sense","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":12},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390666529,"modifiedTime":1666391305332,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"}}
{"_id":"IGOtCKmEAGVQ6nBF","name":"Everstand Stance","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You are wielding a shield.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You brace your shield with both hands, enhancing its potential for both offense and defense. When in this stance, you wield the shield with both hands. When wielding a shield this way, increase the weapon damage die of the shield's boss or spikes by one step, and increase the shield's Hardness by 2 when using the @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.jM72TjJ965jocBV8]{Shield Block} reaction.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.feat-effects.GGebXpRPyONZB3eS]{Stance: Everstand Stance}</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["stance","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"uncommon","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"everstand-stance","schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"You are wielding a shield"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.6GN1zh3RcnZhrzxP"}}}
{"name":"Judgement of Healing","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You&rsquo;ve learned to call on the restorative powers of your faith. You gain the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-spells.0MqXEU7K0OmaorKb]{Judgement of Healing} judgement spell and a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you can regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the Refocus activity to pray to your deity or do service toward their causes.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.k2g5Fq45IuDq6wTE"}},"_id":"ImEXkd9kf2eLuq8b"}
{"name":"Exploit Focus","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your connection to your internal magic has granted you unusual focus. If you have spent at least 2 Focus Points since the last time you Refocused, you recover 2 Focus Points when you Refocus instead of 1.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":12},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390803363,"modifiedTime":1666391305250,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"IpBayYi0LD2B3rRh","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Improved Communal Health","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can direct excess channeled energy outward to benefit an ally. You can grant the Hit Points you would regain from Communal Health to any one creature within the range of your @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.rfZpqmj0AIIdkVIs]{Heal} or @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.szIyEsvihc5e1w8n]{Soothe} spell instead of yourself. You can also use Communal Health when you target only yourself with a heal or soothe spell, though if you do, you must grant the additional healing to someone other than yourself.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":8},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Communal Health"}]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390243339,"modifiedTime":1666391305249,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"It0iRzyWSyOpv9N0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Fuel Magic","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>You are locked to a tradition of magic<br><strong>Trigger </strong>An ally within 30 feet Casts a Spell.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You use your ability to cast any tradition of spell to supplement an ally's spellcasting, providing magical energy for their spells. If you&rsquo;re currently locked to arcane spells, attempt an Arcana check, a Nature check if locked to primal spells, an Occultism check if locked to occult spells, or a Religion check if locked to divine spells using a very high DC for the ally's level, and either spend a Focus Point (if the triggering spell is a focus spell) or expend a spell slot at least 1 level higher than the triggering spell. If you succeed at the check, your ally's spell doesn't cost the Focus Point or spell slot.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":8},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390241993,"modifiedTime":1666391305249,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"JKAswi1RQj0oMcDY","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Second Judgement","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can channel more of your deity&rsquo;s judgement. You can now have a second judgement focus spell active. If you cast a third judgement spell while two are still active, the duration and effect of the oldest judgement spell ends immediately.</p>\n<p>If you have spent at least 2 Focus Points since the last time you Refocused, you recover 2 Focus Points when you Refocus instead of 1.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":10},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O92YHrA6uInCRurA"}},"_id":"KP3XNqPqV67Yt5g6"}
{"_id":"Kd0O6FqVLQgR7vgJ","name":"Focused Studies","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Choose a single tradition. Add two common 10th-level spells of that tradition to your spellbook. You gain a single 10th-level spell slot you can use to cast these spells, using theurge spellcasting. You cannot gain more 10th-level spells, and they can&rsquo;t be used with any abilities that let you change the tradition of a spell, such as Tradition Tinker.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":20},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666391305246,"modifiedTime":1666391305246,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Reach Spell","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can extend the range of your spells. If the next action you use is to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} that has a range, increase that spell's range by 30 feet. As is standard for increasing spell ranges, if the spell normally has a range of touch, you extend its range to 30 feet.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Advanced Player's Guide, Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","metamagic","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"reach-spell","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.BWomK7EVY0WXxWgh"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666388738900,"modifiedTime":1666391305246,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"LsoOyoPNEZF7CCWl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Interweave Dispel","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You have @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.9HpwDN4MYQJnW0LG]{Dispel Magic} prepared</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You weave dispelling energy into a spell, sending both effects at a foe. If your next action is to cast a single-target spell against a creature, and you either hit the foe with the spell attack roll or the foe fails its saving throw, you can cast <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.9HpwDN4MYQJnW0LG]{Dispel Magic}</em> on the foe as a free action, expending a spell slot as normal and targeting one spell effect affecting the foe.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Core Rulebook, Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","metamagic","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"interweave-dispel","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":14},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.bjNeSAldeTzRcEaQ"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390844133,"modifiedTime":1666391305250,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"Mr6W1rjuOMvO9SyM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Communal Health","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You&rsquo;re a conduit for positive energy, and as you channel it through you, it heals some of your minor injuries. When you cast the @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.rfZpqmj0AIIdkVIs]{Heal} or @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.szIyEsvihc5e1w8n]{Soothe} spell to heal a single creature other than yourself, you regain Hit Points equal to the spell level of the spell.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["healing","positive","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":4},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666389823539,"modifiedTime":1666391305247,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"N0xXQBac9FlMg77R","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Scripture of Faith","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You&rsquo;re always ready to pull out any religious scripture of your faith. When you use the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-actions.W2XgBLycybWegHqQ]{Divine Force} activity, you may Interact to draw a scroll with a divine spell as part of the activity. The scroll must be the spell you use with Divine Force.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":4},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hha0LiidoFUaCgML"}},"_id":"NoW22b5kzeSpiOH8"}
{"name":"Exploitive Location","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your magical energy is unpredictable and sometimes has uncontrollable consequences. You gain the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-spells.fVwQpePQyQbF8CUU]{Exploitive Location}&nbsp;exploit spell. Increase the number of Focus Points in your focus pool by 1.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"system.resources.focus.max","value":1}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":6},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390145724,"modifiedTime":1666391305248,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"QA3GHM7bNf0ASCCI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Spellbook Prodigy","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are particularly adept at learning spells to add to your spellbook. You can @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Q5iIYCFdqJFM31GW]{Learn a Spell} in half the time it normally takes. Further, when you roll a critical failure on your check to Learn a Spell, you get a failure instead. When you roll a failure, you can try again after 1 week.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666388777058,"modifiedTime":1666391305247,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"QhIIa2R0K6FKQMcc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Forced Conversion","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You force your will unto others with the power of your strikes. Use the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-actions.W2XgBLycybWegHqQ]{Divine Force} activity. If the Strike hits, the target becomes subject to a 1st level @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.aIHY2DArKFweIrpf]{Command} spell. The level of this effect increases automatically to the same level of your highest spell slot, but it never gains any listed effects for being heightened.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["auditory","enchantment","linguistic","mental","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":4},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":2},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Conversion Inquisition"},{"value":"Divine Force"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9iG5ymoeNXe1xcSu"}},"_id":"QlwgnSMzyhAorH5o"}
{"name":"Zealous Grimoire","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your holy scripture is extensive enough to be used as an actual weapon. You can use a holy text of your faith as a @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.c58wczIzH2gzeXQL]{Club} that always counts as your deity&rsquo;s favored weapon. The grimoire counts as a club for purposes of placing potency and property runes on it.</p>\n<p>Additionally, while holding you grimoire, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Recall Knowledge to identify creatures using a skill related to the subject of the book (usually Religion). This bonus is in addition to any item bonus the book normally gives to the check.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bO4eWoPA0Vt4rM2S"}},"_id":"RiWmC6d10V6l8ujV"}
{"name":"Measured Response","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are trained with any weapon that has the nonlethal trait. In addition, you take no penalty when making a nonlethal attack with your deity&rsquo;s favored weapon without the nonlethal trait</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.h3NpNb2tJNdGk2lV"}},"_id":"STFpqpBOpL8ZqyWQ"}
{"name":"Supreme Cleaving Smite","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Divine wrath floods your body as you attack in an arc in front of you. Use the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-actions.W2XgBLycybWegHqQ]{Divine Force} activity but roll separate Strikes to attack each enemy within your reach or three enemies in your first range increment if using a ranged weapon. This counts as three attacks for your multiple attack penalty, but the penalty doesn't increase until after you make all of your attacks.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you're using a weapon that has the sweep trait, its circumstance bonus applies against all targets. If you&rsquo;re using a ranged weapon, you must be able to attack with it three times without spending any other actions such as having reload 0 or using a returning rune&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":20},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":3},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Cleaving Smite"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6neiSbWnEAtadeRA"}},"_id":"SnJ9cdkz1Lf23BCw"}
{"name":"Magical Reading","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements</strong> Locked into one tradition of spellcasting (see @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-features.SjORb3rT8CPLrhab]{Theurge Spellcasting})</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You use magical reading techniques, aura reading, and other tricks to discover your foe's strengths and weaknesses. Attempt a skill check based on the tradition of spellcasting you are currently in. Attempt an Arcana for arcane spellcasting, Nature for primal spellcasting, Occultism for occult spellcasting, or Religion for divine spellcasting. The GM rolls a secret check of the skill you use against the Deception or Stealth DC (whichever is higher) of an enemy of your choice who is engaged in combat and isn't concealed from you, hidden from you, or undetected by you. The GM might apply a penalty for the distance between you and the<br>enemy. The enemy is then temporarily immune to your Magical Reading for 1 day.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success </strong>The GM chooses and tells you two of the following pieces of information about the enemy: which of the enemy's weaknesses is highest, which of the enemy's saving throws has the lowest modifier, one immunity the enemy has, or which of the enemy's resistances is highest. In the event of a tie, the GM should pick one at random.</p>\n<p><strong>Success </strong>The GM chooses one piece of information from the above list to tell you about the enemy.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure </strong>The GM gives you false information (the GM makes up the information).</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["secret","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":4},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666389828590,"modifiedTime":1666391305247,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"TAssp8LCDGJNdmnH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
