{"name":"Divine Wrack","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your deity wracks those that turn away from your faith with great pain. Once per day, you can cast @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.8Umt1AzYfFbC4fui]{Spellwrack} as an innate divine spell of 5th level. This innate spell automatically heightens to match the highest level spell slot you are capable of casting.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":10},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Heresy Inquisition"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1pH99iYvh5d1jOqw"}},"_id":"X8hZmpptBpiadYRC"}
{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Overwhelming Energy","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You alter your spells to overcome resistances. If the next action you use is to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell}, the spell ignores an amount of the target&rsquo;s resistance to acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic damage equal to your level. This applies to all damage the spell deals, including persistent damage and damage caused by an ongoing effect of the spell, such as the wall created by wall of fire. A creature&rsquo;s immunities are unaffected.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Core Rulebook"},"traits":{"value":["manipulate","metamagic","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"overwhelming-energy","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":10},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.tXNfWDa6P7bCKrCt"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390591836,"modifiedTime":1666391305250,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"YSazv99p7drgU8Li","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Exploit Vulnerability","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Such is your zeal that it can cause wounds to cease healing. Make a Strike. If it hits and deals damage, the target must make a fortitude save against your spell DC. On a failure, any @Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.lR9R5Vld8Eu2Dha5]{Regeneration} the creature possesses ceases to function until the start of your next turn.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":12},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Exploit Weakness"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fgN60ljPO9N2n0xZ"}},"_id":"Zc7MPC8qVusj8BUz"}
{"name":"Obscure Scripture","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>When someone attempts to lie about their conviction to your faith, your breadth of knowledge allows you to see through falsehoods. When you engage in conversation with someone trying to lie to you regarding a religious topic, you use your Religion DC if it is higher than your Perception DC to determine whether they succeed.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qJtsluEPxgpmpWyw"}},"_id":"auHMxztllyvf5gHI"}
{"name":"Exploit Weakness","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your faith is strong enough to bypass normal defenses. When you critically succeed at an attack roll, any damage you deal ignores the highest type of resistance possessed by the target that would apply to the damage of your attack.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":8},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.sHoO0uOM8RxTnvYs"}},"_id":"b9lJEeVvG5SNdL07"}
{"name":"Magical Scribe","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can craft magical scrolls without the @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.xWY5omyIcILNR7y1]{Magical Crafting} feat, but you must still meet any other requirements. When you @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.rmwa3OyhTZ2i2AHl]{Craft} a batch of scrolls, you can make up to six in a batch instead of the usual four per batch.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666389499023,"modifiedTime":1666391305247,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"cXFaaCzGdg7fNAuM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Devour Spell","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>A spell targets you and is the tradition you are locked in or an adjacent one and you critically succeed your save</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You feed on magical energy to the point that you can literally eat spells directed at you. Make a Counteract check. The counteract level is half your level rounded up, and the counteract check modifier is the standard modifier for counteracting with a spell (your Intelligence modifier plus your spellcasting proficiency bonus, plus any bonuses or penalties that specifically apply to counteract checks). You take a -2 penalty to this counteract check if you are not locked into the same tradition as<br>the spell effect.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":14},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actionCategory":{"value":"defensive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390835563,"modifiedTime":1666391305250,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"ceQOEQcFjS7JOf5E","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Divine Conviction","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can fill others with a fraction of your conviction. Once per day, you can cast@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.GYD0XZ4t3tQq6shc]{Zealous Conviction} as an innate divine spell of 5th level. This innate spell automatically heightens to match the highest level spell slot you are capable of casting.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":10},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Conversion Inquisition"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.l5rZt193UiW0AIbb"}},"_id":"f9stLqZWjVhmMp0a"}
{"name":"Divine Avatar","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your deity has rewarded your zeal with raw power. You're permanently @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.nlCjDvLMf2EkV2dl]{Quickened}. You can use your extra action only to Strike or Stride.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":20},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OZBmAQzxMIcyj7xA"}},"_id":"gSCSMxLbjYSCW3DM"}
{"name":"Solo Tactics","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your faith sometimes makes you an outcast and you&rsquo;ve learned to rely on yourself in combat. Make an attack roll to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.HCl3pzVefiv9ZKQW]{Aid}. If you succeed, you can spend a Reaction on your next attack roll to gain the circumstance bonuses listed in the Aid action based on the result of the attack roll for this action.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":8},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EGjcDAlka1on1ryZ"}},"_id":"gVsxnR1glb1Jxnqx"}
{"name":"Forced Truth","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>Your last action was Divine Force and your Strike hit</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Your divine strikes blow away any attempts to deceive you. Use the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-actions.W2XgBLycybWegHqQ]{Divine Force} activity. If the Strike hits, you can make a Counteract check against one illusion or polymorph effect on the target of your Strike. Your Counteract level is equal to the spell used as part of Divine Force.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":4},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JLKmPFxS6k3WbzUk"}},"_id":"h09NMsqL4tykOBbL"}
{"_id":"hg6kGV04dkFRX1Hz","name":"Emblazon Armament","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Carefully etching a sacred image into a physical object, you steel yourself for battle. You can spend 10 minutes emblazoning a symbol of your deity upon a weapon or shield. The symbol doesn't fade until 1 year has passed, but if you Emblazon an Armament, any symbol you previously emblazoned and any symbol already emblazoned on that item instantly disappears. The item becomes a religious symbol of your deity and can be used as a divine focus while emblazoned, and it gains another benefit determined by the type of item. This benefit applies only to followers of the deity the symbol represents.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Shield</strong> The shield gains a +1 status bonus to its Hardness. (This causes it to reduce more damage with the Shield Block reaction.)</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.feat-effects.U1MpMtRnFqEDBJwd]{Weapon}</strong> The wielder gains a +1 status bonus to damage rolls.</li>\n</ul>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["exploration","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"emblazon-armament","schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.7RFjTTzznsdPcaYB"}}}
{"name":"Cleaving Smite","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Divine wrath floods your body as you attack in an arc in front of you. Use the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-actions.W2XgBLycybWegHqQ]{Divine Force} activity but roll separate Strikes to attack two creatures, each of whom must be within your melee reach or your weapons first range increment and adjacent to each other. This counts as two attacks for your multiple attack penalty, but the penalty doesn't increase until after you make both attacks.</p>\n<p>If you're using a weapon that has the sweep trait, its circumstance bonus applies against both targets. If you&rsquo;re using a ranged weapon, you must be able to attack with it twice without spending any other actions such as having reload 0 or using a @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.qlunQzfnzPQpMG6U]{Returning} rune</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":8},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":3},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YDJ3SQ0OPh4rzlNW"}},"_id":"icV0Xrr4vlufHDVl"}
{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Enhanced Familiar","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You infuse your familiar with additional magical energy. You can select four familiar or master abilities each day, instead of two.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.attributes.familiarAbilities.value","priority":9,"value":4}],"slug":"enhanced-familiar","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Familiar"}]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.N7dTFxpjXGn4ddq8"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666389431851,"modifiedTime":1666391305247,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"jgM9pXmbHkceQ0uW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Spell Penetration","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You've studied ways of overcoming the innate magical resistance that dragons, otherworldly beings, and certain other powerful creatures have. Any creature that has a status bonus to saving throws against magic reduces that bonus by 1 against your spells.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Core Rulebook"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"spell-penetration","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.52cygjzHfSD0YhEA"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390182227,"modifiedTime":1666391305249,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"k09267ZPT8hd77Ta","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Judgement of Community","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You&rsquo;ve learned to call on the protective powers of your faith. You gain the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-spells.MSDB55dNQ961aCFp]{Judgement of Community} judgement spell and a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you can regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the Refocus activity to pray to your deity or do service toward their causes.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":6},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3cwKbwM9Uc8aqvT7"}},"_id":"kLkdNnMykvgZ5tqO"}
{"name":"Bend Tradition","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can change the tradition of your spells to avoid certain resistances. If the next action you use is to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell}, you can declare that the spell counts as a tradition adjacent to the one you prepared it as. The spell loses its magical trait associated with a tradition, such as Arcane, and gains the one you declared instead, such as Occult.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","metamagic","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":8},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390240582,"modifiedTime":1666391305249,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"knie0IdC17DR24KQ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Pray for Insight","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can ask your deity for knowledge at a moment's notice. You can use Religion to Recall Knowledge to identify any creature. When you do, roll a @Check[type:flat|dc:11|showDC:all]. On a failure, the action is wasted as your deity remains silent on the matter, but you can try again with future actions.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":12},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Master in Religion"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tKjVzr0nsrkEx665"}},"_id":"leLvniBPZhcAsNRQ"}
{"_id":"mMG2Hlq3Oe2DCU0d","name":"Replenishment of War","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Striking out against your enemies draws praise and protection from your deity. When you damage a creature with a Strike using your deity's favored weapon, you gain a number of temporary Hit Points equal to half your level, or equal to your level if the Strike was a critical hit. These temporary Hit Points last until the start of your next turn.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"replenishment-of-war","schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":14},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.aMef2VM4mSxl0pmy"}}}
{"name":"Sacred Weapon","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your faith further empowers your weapon to be stronger than it appears. Make a Strike with your deity&rsquo;s favored weapon. The damage die of your weapon for this Strike increases by one step (d4 to d6, d6 to d8, d8 to d10, d10 to d12). This increase applies even if the weapon already has an increase from the Deific Weapon class feature.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":8},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.uxCJdK1gBpwlVgv8"}},"_id":"orVdDaz6x4MUjGAF"}
{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","name":"Effortless Concentration","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Trigger</strong> Your turn begins</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You maintain a spell with hardly a thought. You immediately gain the effects of the Sustain a Spell action, allowing you to extend the duration of one of your active class spells.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Pathfinder Advanced Player's Guide"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"effortless-concentration","schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":16},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"free"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"type":"feat","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.rgs6OZJYCgi5At8J"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666391062385,"modifiedTime":1666391305251,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"osOSVwFegWUt4NRD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Limitless Tinkering","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can alter the traditions of more spells. You can now prepare a single spell of each spell level you can cast as a tradition that it is not normally part of.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":18},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Tradition Tinker"}]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666391132847,"modifiedTime":1666391305251,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"qh7yX4LUNH8SMyH5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Third Judgement","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can channel even more of your deity&rsquo;s judgement. You can now have a third judgement focus spell active. If you cast a fourth judgement spell while three are still active, the duration and effect of the oldest judgement spell ends immediately.</p>\n<p>If you have spent at least 3 Focus Points since the last time you Refocused, you recover 3 Focus Points when you Refocus instead of 1.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":18},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Second Judgement"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9SZOMVqMAYEQPcjC"}},"_id":"qvNaNAOaEi3H49ao"}
{"name":"Dangerous Magic","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your legacy grants you great destructive power. When you Cast a Spell from your spell slots, if the spell deals damage and doesn&rsquo;t have a duration, you gain a status bonus to that spell&rsquo;s damage equal to the spell&rsquo;s level.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"FlatModifier","selector":"spell-damage","value":"@spell.level","type":"status","predicate":["item:spell-slot","item:duration:0","damaging-effect"]}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666388778678,"modifiedTime":1666391305245,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"rO0vHeXdCNVp3qWP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Final Judgement","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can proclaim a fatal judgement against your enemies. You gain the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-spells.gGLEDOX5ZN1FsgUH]{Final Judgement} focus spell. Increase the number of Focus Points in your focus pool by 1.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":16},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YtqvVTcxGb2kUV2W"}},"_id":"rWy3LkVVyCTkOsHE"}
