{"_id":"w2Ifh6LlfciUYbJi","name":"Everstand Strike","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/feats/feats.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You are wielding a shield in two hands.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Your follow-up blow leaves you an opening to set your shield. Make a Strike with the wielded shield. If the Strike hits and deals damage, you also @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.xjGwis0uaC2305pm]{Raise your Shield}.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["press","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"uncommon","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":"everstand-strike","schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Everstand Stance "}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.3y459uK2qfWtS9q4"}}}
{"name":"Judgement of Protection","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You&rsquo;ve learned to call on the protective powers of your faith. You gain the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-spells.wEVk7ZSE1QAVrkyH]{Judgement of Protection} judgement spell and a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you can regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the Refocus activity to pray to your deity or do service toward their causes.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3OMWPbSfgQKtCn5k"}},"_id":"xhYH6h9QQgmpQwV7"}
{"name":"Exploitive Spell","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You combine multiple traditions into a single spell, allowing you to cast two spells at once. If the next action you use is to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell}, after that spell resolves, you can Cast another Spell as a free action. This spell must be cast from an adjacent tradition and be a spell that would normally take two actions to cast. Both spells count as being from both traditions.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","metamagic","hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":20},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666391204737,"modifiedTime":1666391305251,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"xmWLT3bTKTiciCnP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Judgement of Haste","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You&rsquo;ve learned to call on the healing powers of your faith. You gain the @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-spells.SORfoyByRnfVLiTp]{Judgement of Haste} judgement spell and a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you can regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the Refocus activity to pray to your deity or do service toward their causes.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["divine","hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":14},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VTYJui1HNM36J8Hj"}},"_id":"y3RW9RcJl7oaScZB"}
{"name":"Barbed Chains","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>Your last action was @Compendium[pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-actions.W2XgBLycybWegHqQ]{Divine Force} and the target of your Strike failed its save</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can empower your chains with barbs of divine energy. The target suffers @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.lDVqvLKA6eF3Df60]{Persistent Damage} equal to your Wisdom modifier and becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.i3OJZU2nk64Df3xm]{Clumsy 1} as long as they are taking this persistent damage. The damage is your choice of either lawful, chaotic, evil, or good so long as your deity has the alignment component you choose.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_zealot"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.769,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-08-20T12:59:34.557-05:00","version":{"schema":null,"foundry":"9.269","system":"3.13.5.16"}}},"level":{"value":4},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Imprisonment Inquisition"}]},"location":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.jIpWVgW7LmKfnHuI"}},"_id":"yLj2UfhVnRpqAdDP"}
{"name":"Boundless Energy","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Raw energy fills you to the brim. Twice per day, you can cast a spell after you&rsquo;ve run out of spell slots of the appropriate spell level; the two spells you cast with this feat must be of different spell levels.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":16},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666391004131,"modifiedTime":1666391305250,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"zJ0m40enayepF6YP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
{"name":"Conjured Scrolls","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","effects":[],"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>During your daily preparations, you can create two temporary scrolls containing spells from your spellbook. These scrolls follow the normal rules for scrolls, with some additional restrictions. Each scroll must be of a different spell level, and both spell levels must be 2 or more levels lower than your highest-level spell. Any scrolls you create this way become non-magical the next time you make your daily preparations. A temporary scroll has no value.</p>\n<p>If you have master proficiency in theurge spell DCs, you can create three temporary scrolls during your daily preparations, and if you have legendary proficiency, you can create four temporary scrolls.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":["hb_theurge"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.847-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"level":{"value":10},"featType":{"value":"class"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Magical Scribe"}]},"location":null},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.2.6","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666390429815,"modifiedTime":1666391305249,"lastModifiedBy":"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx"},"_id":"zyxzPJp3CZSC4Cib","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3}}
